Package org.gwt.mosaic.ui.client.layout

Interface Summary
HasLayoutManager  
LayoutManager Defines the interface for classes that know how to lay out a LayoutPanel.
 

Class Summary
BaseLayout  
BorderLayout A border layout lays out a LayoutPanel, arranging and resizing its widgets to fit in five regions: BorderLayout.BorderLayoutRegion.NORTH, BorderLayout.BorderLayoutRegion.SOUTH, BorderLayout.BorderLayoutRegion.EAST, BorderLayout.BorderLayoutRegion.WEST, and BorderLayout.BorderLayoutRegion.CENTER.
BorderLayoutData  
BoxLayout A layout manager that allows multiple widgets of a LayoutPanel to be laid out either vertically or horizontally.
BoxLayoutData Layout data object for BoxLayout.
FillLayout FillLayout lays out the first visible widget forcing it to completely fill the available space.
FillLayoutData Layout data object for FillLayout.
FormLayout  
GridLayout The GridLayout class is a layout manager that lays out a panel's widgets in a rectangular grid.
GridLayoutData GridLayoutData is the layout data object associated with GridLayout.
LayoutData Base class for all layout data objects.
